## React Rules (react.mdc)

```markdown
---
description: React component conventions
globs: ["**/*.tsx", "**/*.jsx"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# React Standards

## Components
- Use functional components with hooks
- Keep components focused on one responsibility
- Extract custom hooks for reusable logic
- Use memo() only when there's a measured performance need

## State
- Prefer useState for local state
- Use context sparingly (prop drilling is often clearer)
- Keep state as local as possible
- Derive state when possible instead of syncing

## Props
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Destructure props in function signature
- Provide default values when sensible
- Use children prop for composition

## Accessibility
- Add aria-labels to interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Use semantic HTML elements
```

